<subSubSection pageId="90" pageNumber="369" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="90.[797,1390,2862,3285]" lastBlockId="90.[182,1387,3291,3481]" pageId="90" pageNumber="369">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[798,1178,3059,3088]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Reithrodontomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="90" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">Reithrodontomys mexicanus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName box="[1218,1296,3059,3088]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Reithrodontomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="90" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cherrii">cherrii</taxonomicName>
and R. m. garichensis are now recognized as distinct species. Furthermore, R. m. potrerograndei is recognized as subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goodwin" authorityYear="1943" box="[910,1086,3216,3245]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Reithrodontomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="90" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brevirostris">R. brevirostris</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1860" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Reithrodontomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="90" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">Reithrodontomys mexicanus</taxonomicName>
1s in subgenus Aporodon. Based on molecular and morphological evidence, E. Arellano in 2015 concluded that South American subspecies are aligned with R. dariensis, not 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[958,1131,3330,3363]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Reithrodontomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="90" pageNumber="369" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">R. mexicanus</taxonomicName>
, a hypothesis that makes biogeographic sense. Ten subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
